exp2_IntOccDiff

William Sheppard

29/05/2020

This script investigates the effect of removing participants with no interocular difference or large interocular difference on CKAT measures

data: data frame dv: (numeric) the dependent (or outcome) variable name. wid: variable name specifying the case/sample identifier. within: within-subjects factor or grouping variable

Aiming

One-way repeated measures anova dv = MT wid = P_ID_ within = visual condition

All data

Tracking

Three-way repeated measures anova

dv = RMSE wid = P_ID_ within = visual condition, speed, guide

Some conditions are not normally distributed, see qq plot for details

No main effect of eye condition. Main effect of guide and speed, and a sig. guide*speed interaction. Not interested in this effect in this paper, therefore, I am not probing this any further.
